          <h2 class='ui dividing header'>Beautify your home...<a class='anchor' id='carpet'></a></h2>
          <p>
            Vacuuming your carpet regularly is the first step in keeping your carpet looking beautiful.  Many carpet manufacturers recommend professional carpet cleaning every 12 to 18 months.  Choice of the proper carpet cleaning equipment and system is important.   Some systems may leave residues which promote re-soiling and defeat the whole purpose of cleaning.
            CIA Services uses an advanced truck-mounted hot water extraction system.  This process consists of spraying a heated solution of water and detergent into the carpet pile.   The solution is immediately extracted with a powerful vacuum into a holding tank.   This is done by a truck-mounted unit outside the home with only the hose and wand are brought inside your home.  In high-rises, where a truck-mounted unit cannot reach, a portable, self-contained system is used.
          </p>
          <p>
            This approach has excellent results for cleaning moderate to heavily soiled carpet.  The operator can observe when the solution is soil free and the drying time is somewhat less than with the shampoo process.
          </p>
          <h3 class='ui header'>Cleaning area & oriental rugs...</h3>
          <p>
            ...is usually done at our facility which has been designed for specialized cleaning of loose or valuable rugs.  Following are the steps we take to clean your rugs in our facility:
            <ul>
              <li>Inspect and then send your rug through a duster to remove dry, embedded soil</li>
              <li>Pre-spot if necessary</li>
              <li>Hand-shampoo</li>
              <li>Rinse using cold water and then remove the excess water</li>
              <li>Groom your rug so that the nap / pile is going in one direction</li>
              <li>Carefully dry your rug in a climate controlled drying chamber</li>
              <li>Final quality inspection</li>
            </ul>
          </p>
