          <h3 class='ui header'>Care of Hardwood Floors</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Place area rugs or mats at entrances to protect wood floors from scratches. </li>
            <li>Sweep wood floors regularly with a soft bristle broom or vacuum attachment to remove loose dirt before it can scratch the surface.</li>
            <li>When moving furniture across a wood floor, either pick it up or place protective pads between the floor and the furniture.</li>
            <li>Never clean a hardwood floor with water, soaps or detergents.</li>
            <li>Most food spills will not harm a wood surface, but they should be cleaned up promptly with a paper towel or dry cloth.</li>
            <li>Never use vinyl or tile floor care products on hardwood floors.</li>
            <li>Keep potted plants off a wood floor so condensation does not build up and damage the floor.</li>
            <li>Be sure to follow the manufacturer's guidelines for the care of your floor. </li>
          </ul>
